---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="For Business Owners - Waterloo Track" description="Know if your ads actually work in 10 minutes. Stop paying for marketing based on faith.">
	<main>
		<!-- Hero Section -->
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h1>Your Ads Are Either Making You Money<br>Or Bleeding You Dry.</h1>
				<p>But you have no idea which is which. Your platforms say everything's great. Your bank account tells a different story.</p>
				<a href="#truth" class="btn">See the Truth</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Problem Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The Expensive Guessing Game You're Playing</h2>
				<p>Facebook says your ads generated $50k in revenue. Google claims $30k. Your actual revenue? $80k.</p>
				<p><strong>So which campaigns are actually working?</strong></p>
				
				<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 30px 0;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Here's what's probably happening:</strong></p>
					<ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
						<li>Your best campaigns look terrible in the data (so you kill them)</li>
						<li>Your worst campaigns look amazing (so you scale them up)</li>
						<li>You're spending more every month but seeing less profit</li>
						<li>Your marketing budget feels like throwing money into a black hole</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem;">It's not your fault. The tracking is just broken.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Money Problem Section -->
		<section id="truth" class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The Real Cost of Broken Attribution</h2>
				<p>Let's talk numbers. Because that's what matters to you.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin: 40px 0;">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #eed36b;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Wasted Ad Spend</h3>
						<p>Industry average: 30% of ad spend goes to campaigns that don't work. On a $10k/month budget, that's $3,600 down the drain every month.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #eed36b;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Killed Winners</h3>
						<p>Your best campaigns get shut down because they "look bad" in the data. You're literally stopping the things that make you money.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #eed36b;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Scaled Losers</h3>
						<p>Your worst campaigns get more budget because they "look good." Every dollar you add to these campaigns is money you'll never see again.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div style="background: #333; color: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; margin-top: 40px;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 15px;"><strong>Bottom line:</strong></p>
					<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #eed36b; font-weight: 700;">Broken attribution costs the average business $43k per year in wasted ad spend.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Solution Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>What If You Could See Exactly Which Ads Make You Money?</h2>
				<p>Not in 6 weeks. Not after hiring a consultant. Not after reading seventeen blog posts about "advanced attribution modeling."</p>
				<p><strong>In 10 minutes. Today.</strong></p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 40px; margin: 40px 0; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));">
					<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Stop the Bleed</h3>
						<p>See which campaigns are actually losing money (even if the platforms say they're profitable) and turn them off immediately.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Scale the Winners</h3>
						<p>Find your hidden profitable campaigns and give them the budget they deserve. Watch your profit margins actually improve.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Make Real Decisions</h3>
						<p>Base your marketing decisions on actual profit, not vanity metrics that make you feel good but drain your bank account.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- How It Works Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>How This Actually Works (Without the Technical BS)</h2>
				<p>You don't need to understand server-side tracking or first-party data collection. You just need to see which ads make you money.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin: 40px 0;">
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: center;">
						<div style="background: #7cd3d2; color: white; width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">1</div>
						<div>
							<h3>We Set Up Your Tracking</h3>
							<p>Takes 30 minutes. We handle all the technical stuff. You don't touch a thing.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: center;">
						<div style="background: #7cd3d2; color: white; width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">2</div>
						<div>
							<h3>Your Data Gets Clean</h3>
							<p>Our system captures every conversion that Facebook and Google miss. No more blind spots.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: center;">
						<div style="background: #7cd3d2; color: white; width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">3</div>
						<div>
							<h3>You See What's Really Working</h3>
							<p>Dashboard shows you profit per campaign. Green means scale up. Red means turn off. That's it.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 50px;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Total time investment:</strong> 10 minutes to look at your dashboard once a week.</p>
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem;"><strong>Result:</strong> Stop wasting money on ads that don't work.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Success Stories Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Businesses That Stopped Throwing Money Away</h2>
				<p>These aren't case studies. They're business owners like you who got tired of guessing.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #7cd3d2;">
						<p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; font-style: italic;">"First week, killed three campaigns that were bleeding money. Platforms said they were 'profitable.' Real data showed they were costing me $8k/month. That alone paid for the system for two years."</p>
						<p style="font-weight: 600;">E-commerce Store Owner</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #7cd3d2;">
						<p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; font-style: italic;">"Found out my 'worst performing' campaign was actually my best. Had been about to shut it down. Instead, tripled the budget. Revenue up 60% in six weeks."</p>
						<p style="font-weight: 600;">SaaS Founder</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #7cd3d2;">
						<p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; font-style: italic;">"Went from burning $15k/month on ads with no clear ROI to spending $12k/month and making 3x the profit. Same traffic, better campaigns, real data."</p>
						<p style="font-weight: 600;">Local Business Owner</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Investment Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>What This Actually Costs</h2>
				<p>Think about this: if broken attribution wastes just 20% of your ad spend, how much are you losing every month?</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin: 40px 0; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-center;">
						<h3>$5k/month ad spend</h3>
						<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #7cd3d2; font-weight: 700; margin: 15px 0;">$1,000/month</p>
						<p>wasted on broken attribution</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-center;">
						<h3>$10k/month ad spend</h3>
						<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #7cd3d2; font-weight: 700; margin: 15px 0;">$2,000/month</p>
						<p>wasted on broken attribution</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-center;">
						<h3>$25k/month ad spend</h3>
						<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #7cd3d2; font-weight: 700; margin: 15px 0;">$5,000/month</p>
						<p>wasted on broken attribution</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div style="text-align: center; background: #333; color: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">Our attribution platform costs a fraction of what you're already wasting.</p>
					<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: #eed36b;">If it doesn't save you more than it costs in the first 30 days, we'll refund everything.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- CTA Section -->
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Ready to Stop Guessing and Start Knowing?</h2>
				<p>Free attribution audit. We'll show you exactly where your money is going. No commitment.</p>
				<p>If we can't find at least $1,000/month in wasted ad spend, the audit is free.</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="btn">Get Your Free Audit</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Questions Every Business Owner Asks</h2>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"How is this different from what Facebook and Google already show me?"</h3>
						<p>Facebook and Google only see about 70% of your conversions because of iOS updates and privacy settings. We capture everything, so you see the full picture.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"Is this going to break my existing setup?"</h3>
						<p>Nope. We add tracking alongside what you already have. Nothing gets turned off or changed. If you want to remove it later, takes 5 minutes.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"Do I need a tech person to manage this?"</h3>
						<p>No. We set it up, we maintain it. You just look at the dashboard and make decisions. Green campaigns get more budget. Red campaigns get turned off.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"What if I'm spending less than $5k/month on ads?"</h3>
						<p>Then you probably can't afford to waste any of it. Even if you save just 10% of a $2k/month budget, that's $2,400/year back in your pocket.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Final Push Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
				<h2>The Choice Is Pretty Simple</h2>
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 40px; margin: 40px 0; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));">
					<div style="padding: 30px;">
						<h3 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Keep Doing What You're Doing</h3>
						<ul style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
							<li>Keep guessing which ads work</li>
							<li>Keep wasting 20-30% of your ad budget</li>
							<li>Keep scaling campaigns that lose money</li>
							<li>Keep killing campaigns that make money</li>
							<li>Keep wondering why your marketing doesn't work</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 20px;">Or Get Real Data</h3>
						<ul style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
							<li>See exactly which ads make you money</li>
							<li>Stop wasting money on campaigns that don't work</li>
							<li>Scale the campaigns that actually drive profit</li>
							<li>Make marketing decisions based on facts</li>
							<li>Finally see ROI that makes sense</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 40px;">Every day you wait is another day of wasted ad spend.</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 20px;">Get Your Free Attribution Audit</a>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>